WEBVTT

00:02.003 --> 00:03.723
NARRATOR:
<i>Previously on</i> The Vampire Diaries:

00:03.796 --> 00:05.965
ELENA:
Kai is trapped in a 1903 prison world.

00:06.173 --> 00:08.134
- So Kai is gone?
- As in, for good.

00:08.342 --> 00:09.622
- I'm pregnant.
ALARIC: Marry me.

00:09.677 --> 00:11.804
- Yes.
- I've always wanted a family.

00:12.013 --> 00:13.472
It's never gonna happen for me.

00:13.681 --> 00:16.308
JO: Before the 1900s,
Lily fell in with a group of witches...

00:16.517 --> 00:19.520
...that were cast out of the Gemini Coven.
Heretics are ruthless.

00:19.729 --> 00:23.065
Vampires with witch power,
they can never be allowed to escape.

00:23.274 --> 00:26.569
ENZO: You turned me and left me on
a passenger ship full of headless corpses.

00:26.777 --> 00:30.531
No, the night I turned you, my friends
and I were captured by the Gemini Coven.

00:30.740 --> 00:34.160
The Ascendant is the only thing
that can get my people back.

00:34.368 --> 00:36.704
- If I was human, we wouldn't work.
- Exactly.

00:36.912 --> 00:39.582
The cure to vampirism.
I left it out for you to find.

00:39.832 --> 00:42.001
Since Damon was never
going to offer it to you.

00:42.209 --> 00:45.671
- Why would you keep it a secret?
- I'm so in love. I don't wanna lose you.

00:45.880 --> 00:47.423
I don't want to live without you.

00:47.673 --> 00:50.342
You're gonna take the cure.
I'm gonna take it with you.

01:00.186 --> 01:01.228
[PHONE BUZZES]

01:04.397 --> 01:07.902
You've bailed on your shift, and you're
headed here to help me grade papers.

01:08.110 --> 01:09.612
Aw, you know me so well.

01:09.820 --> 01:13.240
Except I'd rather be covered
in Mrs. Robertson's intestinal bile...

01:13.449 --> 01:14.784
...than grading term papers.

01:15.034 --> 01:17.203
- I'll take that as a no.
JO [OVER PHONE]: <i>I just realized...</i>

01:17.411 --> 01:19.997
...that tonight is my last shift
as a single woman.

01:20.206 --> 01:23.459
- I can't wait to marry you.
- And I am counting the days.

01:23.667 --> 01:25.211
Me too.

01:51.570 --> 01:52.613
[YELLS]

01:56.075 --> 01:57.409
MAN:
Dr. Laughlin?

01:57.618 --> 01:59.453
- Yes?
- Hi, I'm Officer Baker.

01:59.662 --> 02:02.748
- Is there somewhere private we can speak?
- Sure.

02:06.252 --> 02:08.711
- What's this about?
- Regarding Professor Saltzman.

02:08.920 --> 02:12.216
- I understand you are engaged to be married.
- Is something wrong?

02:16.095 --> 02:17.138
Nope.

02:19.932 --> 02:22.226
Everything is just right.

02:22.393 --> 02:26.772
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa! Whoa! Wow. Uh...
Oh, my God, no. I don't think so...

02:26.981 --> 02:29.191
ELENA AND BONNIE [IN UNISON]: Surprise!
Whoa!

02:29.358 --> 02:30.901
[ALL LAUGHING AND CHEERING]

02:31.068 --> 02:33.028
No, no, no, this can't be happening.

02:33.195 --> 02:34.835
[UPBEAT DANCE MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

02:34.905 --> 02:37.283
Yeah.

02:37.491 --> 02:40.244
- Happy bachelorette!
- Happy bachelorette!

02:40.411 --> 02:41.579
[GRUNTS]

02:42.621 --> 02:43.914
What the hell is going on?

02:44.123 --> 02:47.126
ALL [IN UNISON]:
Happy bachelor party!

02:47.293 --> 02:48.586
[ALL CHEERING]

02:48.752 --> 02:50.796
[UPBEAT ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

02:59.763 --> 03:01.015
[ALL LAUGHING]

03:01.182 --> 03:03.017
An entire diner to ourselves.
Actual heaven.

03:03.225 --> 03:05.394
Caroline would be planning a spa day.

03:05.603 --> 03:07.938
- But now she's MIA.
JO: Understandable.

03:08.147 --> 03:11.942
- Considering.
- So I figured we'd just stuff our faces.

03:12.151 --> 03:14.445
- You're geniuses, ah.
- Except aren't you a vegetarian?

03:15.571 --> 03:18.240
- Bonnie, don't ruin it.
- That's not a Gardenburger.

03:18.449 --> 03:21.243
The baby is not okay
with the no-meat thing.

03:21.452 --> 03:24.455
Besides, it's my party,
and I'll eat what I want to.

03:24.705 --> 03:26.707
- I do wish this was vodka though.
- Right?

03:26.916 --> 03:29.418
Hey, I don't want to know
what Ric's doing, do I?

03:29.960 --> 03:32.421
- Probably at the movies.
- Yeah, or mini golf.

03:32.588 --> 03:33.839
- Heh.
- Uh-huh.

03:34.006 --> 03:35.090
Mm.

03:35.257 --> 03:36.383
I need ketchup.

03:36.550 --> 03:38.719
[MELLOW ROCK MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

03:44.308 --> 03:46.268
BONNIE:
So are we gonna talk about it?

03:46.435 --> 03:48.062
- What?
- Seriously.

03:48.270 --> 03:51.315
You're gonna make your best friend
have to pry it out of you?

03:51.565 --> 03:54.276
- I know about the cure, Elena.
- You do?

03:56.153 --> 03:57.613
[WHISPERS]
How is that even possible?

03:57.780 --> 04:01.951
Damon called and told me everything, including
his insane plan to take it with you.

04:02.117 --> 04:04.437
[IN NORMAL VOICE]: Damon called you?
- He needed to talk...

04:04.578 --> 04:06.997
...after you left without telling him
what you were thinking.

04:07.206 --> 04:09.667
- That's not exactly how it happened.
- And I quote:

04:09.875 --> 04:13.212
"She stared at me like I was an alien
and teleported out of the room."

04:13.462 --> 04:17.132
Damon stands in front of you and tells you
he wants to become human again.

04:17.298 --> 04:18.801
Wouldn't you freak out?

04:21.178 --> 04:23.806
I just... I needed some time to process.

04:24.014 --> 04:27.726
I mean, 24 hours ago I didn't even think
it was possible to become human again.

04:27.977 --> 04:30.980
- But you want to be a human again.
- Yeah.

04:31.188 --> 04:32.982
Well, I did.

04:33.148 --> 04:36.485
Ah, honestly, it's all just
very complicated right now.

04:38.904 --> 04:40.906
You guys aren't full, are you?

04:42.366 --> 04:43.492
[CHUCKLES]

04:43.659 --> 04:45.828
What do you mean
you offered to take the cure?

04:45.995 --> 04:48.330
I was standing there,
and it just sort of came out.

04:48.539 --> 04:51.500
- Okay, so how the hell does that even work?
- It's easy.

04:51.667 --> 04:54.003
Elena guzzles it, goes back
to her old human self.

04:54.169 --> 04:56.672
I feed on her. As long
as no one sucks it out of me...

04:56.880 --> 04:59.341
...then we grow old
and die of the common cold.

04:59.550 --> 05:02.553
- So you screwed up, and you're freaking out.
- I didn't screw up.

05:02.761 --> 05:05.931
Damon, if you take that cure,
you can never be a vampire ever again.

05:06.515 --> 05:07.683
All right?

05:07.850 --> 05:10.853
Listen to me. You're writing checks
your ass can't cash.

05:11.061 --> 05:13.439
- Now you're getting cold feet.
- Are you projecting?

05:13.689 --> 05:16.734
- You seriously want to be a human?
- I want to be with Elena.

05:16.942 --> 05:19.153
- What did Stefan say?
- Do you want to spend...

05:19.361 --> 05:23.365
...your last night as a single man
debating my existential crisis?

05:23.574 --> 05:25.409
Damon, tell me you told your brother...

05:25.659 --> 05:28.662
...of 166 years
that you're planning on becoming human.

05:29.997 --> 05:31.040
I will.

05:32.041 --> 05:33.584
Eventually.

05:33.751 --> 05:35.544
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

05:37.171 --> 05:38.213
To you.

05:41.258 --> 05:43.552
[ALL CHEERING]

05:51.310 --> 05:52.394
Sorry I'm late.

05:52.561 --> 05:56.398
Well, considering the guy who lives here
tried to kill us, I don't blame you.

05:56.565 --> 06:00.319
- Yeah, but we're here for Ric, right?
- I'm here for the free booze.

06:00.527 --> 06:01.904
Ooh.

06:02.071 --> 06:04.573
Beer plus meds equals
another trip to the hospital.

06:04.740 --> 06:06.075
You chose now to learn math?

06:06.283 --> 06:08.077
[FOOTSTEPS]

06:09.244 --> 06:11.789
- Who the hell invited you?
- Damon.

06:12.414 --> 06:14.500
I've never been to a bachelor party before.

06:16.001 --> 06:17.795
I can see the appeal.

06:18.003 --> 06:21.215
- Where's Stefan?
- Don't know. Don't care.

06:28.138 --> 06:30.766
CAROLINE [ON RECORDER]: <i>Hey, it's Caroline.
But you knew that because you called.</i>

06:30.974 --> 06:33.811
<i>So leave a message,
and I'll call you back. Bye.</i>

06:34.019 --> 06:35.729
You're so happy in your voice-mail.

06:35.938 --> 06:39.441
Speaking of happy, uh, that thumping bass
you hear in the background...

06:39.608 --> 06:41.443
...that's, um, Damon's genius idea...

06:41.652 --> 06:44.488
...to host Ric's bachelor party.

06:44.738 --> 06:47.241
Despite the fact
that our mother apparently lives here.

06:47.449 --> 06:51.620
Who I've been ducking, by the way,
in case you haven't noticed.

06:52.121 --> 06:53.956
I guess what I'm saying is call me back.

06:54.164 --> 06:56.542
Otherwise I'm gonna start running
out of reasons...

06:56.792 --> 07:01.130
...to avoid everything that is going on
in my life right now.

07:01.296 --> 07:05.050
Kind of like what you're doing,
which is completely understandable.

07:05.300 --> 07:09.304
But just really crappy timing
for me and my problems.

07:10.806 --> 07:12.641
You should be here.

07:13.851 --> 07:15.310
Come home.

07:17.354 --> 07:19.398
That was utterly adorable.

07:20.149 --> 07:23.819
- What are you doing in my bedroom?
- There are a number of places I'd rather be.

07:24.027 --> 07:27.197
Strapped to a gurney
having my spleen cut out, for instance.

07:27.406 --> 07:28.991
Unfortunately for me...

07:29.158 --> 07:31.660
...I'm here because your mother
needs your help.

07:32.369 --> 07:33.662
My mother?

07:33.871 --> 07:36.165
Apparently her beloved Ascendant's
been destroyed.

07:36.373 --> 07:39.376
She's in bad shape.
Could use a bit of your time.

07:41.295 --> 07:43.839
What the hell do you know
about my mother?

07:44.006 --> 07:46.008
[ALL CHATTERING]

07:53.849 --> 07:56.643
[HEART BEATING]

08:29.259 --> 08:31.345
- Hello, Mother.
- Ah.

08:32.929 --> 08:36.265
I think it's time you and I have a talk.

08:41.813 --> 08:43.774
LILY:
This is entirely unnecessary.

08:43.982 --> 08:47.986
- I was merely getting a breath of fresh air.
- Hmm.

08:50.364 --> 08:52.282
What you got there? A junkie tic?

08:53.492 --> 08:56.286
I have the same thing.
It's funny how that works, isn't it?

08:57.120 --> 09:01.083
What is this? Some kind
of mother-son bonding experiment?

09:01.291 --> 09:03.627
No. You made your feelings
for me perfectly clear...

09:03.835 --> 09:06.880
...when you had to spin a web of lies
to snap my humanity back on.

09:07.130 --> 09:10.676
I don't know what Enzo told you,
but I assure you I'm fine.

09:10.884 --> 09:12.564
STEFAN:
Yeah, Enzo told me a lot of things.

09:12.719 --> 09:17.349
Including that after losing all hope
of getting your friends back...

09:17.599 --> 09:19.685
...you went off the deep end last night.

09:22.312 --> 09:23.647
A momentary lapse.

09:23.814 --> 09:27.818
I figured since you passed the Ripper gene
on to me... Thank you for that, by the way.

09:28.986 --> 09:32.823
- We could talk about it. You know, ahem...
- There's nothing to talk about.

09:33.031 --> 09:37.160
...personally, when I start feeling
like I'm gonna go over the edge...

09:37.327 --> 09:40.747
...I begin to salivate
in the back of my mouth.

09:41.248 --> 09:42.624
Does that ever happen to you?

09:42.833 --> 09:46.378
And then my veins,
they begin to itch uncontrollably...

09:46.628 --> 09:48.714
...and the hunger consumes me.

09:49.172 --> 09:51.008
Every sound.

09:51.174 --> 09:52.259
Every scent.

09:53.218 --> 09:56.346
The world around me falls apart.

09:56.513 --> 10:00.851
And all I can hear is the pulsing
of someone's blood.

10:01.018 --> 10:04.021
And all I feel is that it belongs to me.

10:08.358 --> 10:10.485
- Huh?
- Heh.

10:11.361 --> 10:14.781
But I guess you don't have that problem.
Right?

10:18.535 --> 10:20.078
MATT:
Ah-ha.

10:20.287 --> 10:23.123
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

10:23.749 --> 10:26.543
<i>It's kind of crazy that we might have
Missed each other by chance</i>

10:26.752 --> 10:29.588
Drinking yourself to death.
That your big plan for the future?

10:29.796 --> 10:33.675
Just taking a page from your playbook.
Oh, sorry. All the pages.

10:35.552 --> 10:38.180
How about we get out of here? Come on.

10:38.930 --> 10:40.807
I'll drive you home.

10:41.808 --> 10:44.227
How's the deputy training program?

10:46.730 --> 10:48.231
Is that why you're being a dick?

10:48.982 --> 10:52.986
Part of it. Remember, I'm on injured
reserve, so you'll have to fill me in.

10:54.071 --> 10:56.823
Deputy Taylor finally stopped
calling me Cupcake.

10:57.074 --> 10:58.200
I guess that's progress.

10:58.408 --> 11:01.411
Maybe that's because Deputy Taylor's
on medical leave for a week.

11:01.578 --> 11:04.623
- After you kicked his ass in front of trainees.
- He had it coming.

11:05.916 --> 11:09.461
What the hell is wrong with you?
Are you that incapable of not raging out?

11:09.670 --> 11:12.089
This was a chance
to do something with your life.

11:12.255 --> 11:15.258
No. That's what it is for you.
Because I realized, one day...

11:15.801 --> 11:18.261
...doing this job might mean
I have to shoot someone.

11:18.428 --> 11:21.181
To kill them. And I don't ever
want to be a werewolf again.

11:22.599 --> 11:24.434
It doesn't have to be like that, Ty.

11:25.227 --> 11:26.770
[GRUNTS]

11:27.104 --> 11:30.107
- You just need some self-control.
- Watch yourself, Matt.

11:30.691 --> 11:32.234
Control it, Ty.

11:34.778 --> 11:36.446
[BOTH GRUNTING AND PANTING]

11:40.992 --> 11:42.077
Not worth it.

11:48.834 --> 11:50.335
[ALL SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

11:50.502 --> 11:52.838
Where are you? Tell me
you were with a stripper.

11:53.088 --> 11:55.632
Picture that, and then picture
the exact opposite.

11:55.799 --> 11:57.300
I'm with our mother.

11:57.467 --> 11:59.511
DAMON:
<i>Now I don't want to picture anything.</i>

11:59.761 --> 12:01.805
Did you know she was the one
who turned Enzo?

12:02.013 --> 12:04.141
That's mathematically impossible.

12:04.307 --> 12:06.309
- Enzo turned in 19...
- 1903.

12:06.518 --> 12:09.479
Apparently they were on a boat together
back to New York Harbor.

12:09.730 --> 12:11.481
He was sick, and she took pity on him.

12:11.732 --> 12:14.276
<i>We thought she didn't have
a maternal bone in her body.</i>

12:14.484 --> 12:16.820
She has a little bit
of a Ripper thing going on.

12:16.987 --> 12:19.489
STEFAN: <i>That stunt with
the Ascendant put her in a blood tizzy.</i>

12:19.740 --> 12:23.160
Well, then why is she out and about?
Lock her ass up and rejoin the party.

12:23.368 --> 12:25.996
Yeah, I will if it comes to that. Ah.

12:26.621 --> 12:27.664
Anything else?

12:27.831 --> 12:29.458
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

12:29.624 --> 12:31.001
Nope.

12:31.334 --> 12:33.003
Just love to Mom, heh.

12:33.170 --> 12:34.254
Kidding.

12:35.213 --> 12:36.465
[LINE DISCONNECTS]

12:37.841 --> 12:41.052
See, ah? Now, that's what I call
a missed opportunity.

12:41.303 --> 12:45.348
Perfect time to tell your brother you're
hanging up your fangs for a pair of khakis.

12:45.557 --> 12:47.768
No idea what you're talking about.

12:47.976 --> 12:49.644
Yes, you do.

12:49.895 --> 12:52.355
I might have plied Alaric
with enough alcohol...

12:52.564 --> 12:54.399
...to slur the news into my ear.

12:54.649 --> 12:58.779
Well, you are the last person who gets to
criticize me for withholding information...

12:58.987 --> 13:00.822
...my brother from the same mother.

13:02.407 --> 13:04.743
- You were gonna tell me Lily turned you?
- Yeah.

13:04.951 --> 13:07.287
Once you mastered the art
of returning phone calls.

13:07.537 --> 13:10.707
- I've been busy.
- What, with the prospect of taking the cure?

13:10.874 --> 13:13.168
No point agonizing.
You won't go through with it.

13:13.376 --> 13:14.795
Says who?

13:15.170 --> 13:16.546
You.

13:16.880 --> 13:19.800
You're selfish, Damon.
Being human isn't what you really want.

13:21.301 --> 13:24.554
Don't get me wrong, I like that about you.
A man should be consistent.

13:24.721 --> 13:27.724
But take it from someone
who you left to burn to death...

13:27.891 --> 13:30.143
...in order to save your own skin.

13:30.310 --> 13:31.353
[CHUCKLES]

13:31.520 --> 13:32.604
No one changes that much.

13:33.230 --> 13:36.399
Not even under the magical influence
of Elena Gilbert.

13:37.067 --> 13:39.194
Anyway, cheers, mate.

13:43.406 --> 13:46.952
[OVER SPEAKERS]
<i>You've expressed explicitly</i>

13:47.118 --> 13:50.247
<i>Your contempt for matrimony</i>

13:50.455 --> 13:53.708
So, basically, Damon did the vampire
version of a marriage proposal...

13:53.917 --> 13:55.627
...and you just walked away?

13:55.836 --> 13:59.589
I said I would think about it. Why are we
talking about me? This is your party, heh.

13:59.798 --> 14:01.091
Trust me.

14:01.299 --> 14:02.926
I'd much rather talk about that...

14:03.093 --> 14:06.513
...than the fact that I have yet to find
a non-hideous wedding gown.

14:06.763 --> 14:10.100
I can't ask my sister to be my maid
of honor. She won't return my calls.

14:10.267 --> 14:13.979
Or the fact that I cannot stop eating.
Literally.

14:14.229 --> 14:15.522
Like, ever.

14:15.772 --> 14:17.232
So big decision.

14:17.983 --> 14:20.610
- Go.
- I think you should take it. Decision made.

14:20.777 --> 14:22.445
[CHUCKLES]

14:22.612 --> 14:24.489
What if I miss the perks?

14:24.739 --> 14:27.325
Like compelling the owner
of a diner to close early.

14:27.534 --> 14:28.618
Or what if I get sick?

14:28.827 --> 14:31.121
Or what if human you
doesn't love Damon anymore?

14:34.624 --> 14:35.750
Someone had to say it.

14:35.959 --> 14:38.545
That's ridiculous.
Being supernatural doesn't change you.

14:38.795 --> 14:42.257
I should know. I'm an ex-witch
who's about to marry an ex-vampire.

14:42.465 --> 14:44.134
You know who you are, what you want.

14:44.301 --> 14:46.678
Love's always gonna require
a huge leap of faith.

14:46.887 --> 14:50.307
A big, scary leap over a hot pit of lava.
You might end up heartbroken...

14:50.473 --> 14:53.810
...but you might be the happiest person
on the face of the earth.

14:53.977 --> 14:55.979
Personally, I'm glad I took that leap.

14:57.689 --> 14:59.107
[PHONE BUZZES]

15:00.025 --> 15:01.818
Speak of the devil.

15:03.695 --> 15:06.656
Let me guess. You got a lap dance,
and now you feel guilty.

15:06.865 --> 15:09.492
DAMON [OVER PHONE]: <i>How'd you know?</i>
- Heh, very funny.

15:09.701 --> 15:13.663
You may have partied us under the table,
but at least I'm on a junk food high.

15:13.830 --> 15:17.000
<i>Is that why you're walking around town
eating French fries?</i>

15:18.293 --> 15:19.336
<i>Look up.</i>

15:21.838 --> 15:23.673
[CHUCKLES]

15:24.049 --> 15:27.010
- What are you doing up there?
- I'm just clearing my head, ah.

15:27.177 --> 15:30.764
I asked a girl a big question last night.
She just sort of left me hanging.

15:30.931 --> 15:33.683
- Ugh, what a flake.
- That's all right.

15:33.892 --> 15:36.353
She's probably just doing
some soul-searching.

15:36.519 --> 15:37.687
[SIGHS]

15:38.563 --> 15:40.815
- Want some?
- You deliver?

15:45.862 --> 15:48.365
- Ugh.
- See? Sublimating can be fun.

15:49.866 --> 15:51.868
- You're mocking me.
- I am not mocking you.

15:52.035 --> 15:56.957
I'm teaching you how to divert an instinctual
impulse into a socially acceptable activity.

15:57.207 --> 15:59.876
Look, it's either this or squirrel blood.

16:00.085 --> 16:02.045
Unless you're a rabbit person.

16:02.212 --> 16:04.381
You ever try to hunt a rabbit? Humbling.

16:04.547 --> 16:08.385
Imagine cherishing something
for 150 years.

16:08.551 --> 16:11.221
And then imagine that
being ripped away from you.

16:11.429 --> 16:13.098
Believe me, it's devastating.

16:13.556 --> 16:15.558
My friends are gone. Let me grieve.

16:15.767 --> 16:17.978
Your grief is attracting
a lot of attention.

16:18.228 --> 16:21.564
And you're lucky I'm not Damon.
You would be locked in a cell by now.

16:23.650 --> 16:24.734
But not you.

16:25.443 --> 16:27.570
You feel the need to connect.

16:28.571 --> 16:31.491
Or is this strictly
a Ripper-to-Ripper pep talk?

16:31.741 --> 16:32.784
Reformed Ripper.

16:33.660 --> 16:37.998
Who happens to think this relationship
is worth saving.

16:42.377 --> 16:45.130
No. No, I can't do this.

16:46.715 --> 16:48.258
You were the only one...

16:48.758 --> 16:51.219
...who was able to flip
my humanity back on.

16:51.428 --> 16:53.596
- Damon fed me a story.
- And it worked.

16:53.763 --> 16:55.765
All I'm saying is maybe, deep down...

16:56.891 --> 17:00.020
...you still feel something for me.

17:03.273 --> 17:05.817
Stefan, the woman who raised you...

17:06.067 --> 17:09.654
...lived under the hand
of a cheating, abusive husband.

17:09.904 --> 17:11.740
She was weak.

17:11.948 --> 17:13.742
She got sick and died.

17:13.950 --> 17:15.785
And then a new Lily was born.

17:15.952 --> 17:20.540
A powerful Lily who took what she wanted
and found a family that embraced her.

17:21.790 --> 17:23.542
So when I look at you, it's...

17:24.044 --> 17:26.171
It's not that I don't love you.

17:27.338 --> 17:30.800
It's that I'm reminded
of that pathetic woman...

17:31.259 --> 17:33.928
...when all I want to do
is forget that she ever existed.

17:37.640 --> 17:39.476
Well, then, let's...

17:39.934 --> 17:40.977
...start over.

17:41.603 --> 17:42.937
Clean slate.

17:43.146 --> 17:46.483
Let me help you get through this.

17:46.691 --> 17:48.568
We can start something new. Just...

17:50.862 --> 17:52.655
...you have to trust me.

17:54.657 --> 17:57.786
You never could look me in the eye
when you were telling me a lie.

17:58.495 --> 18:00.955
[ALL GRUNTING]

18:07.337 --> 18:08.963
Sorry about the mess.

18:09.506 --> 18:10.673
[PANTING]

18:18.431 --> 18:22.185
ELENA: I love it up here.
- Well, soak it in while you can.

18:22.393 --> 18:24.104
Load up on fries.

18:24.312 --> 18:26.689
- Because trans-fat is no friend to humans.
- Heh.

18:32.570 --> 18:35.406
Did you mean it when you told me
you'd take the cure?

18:35.615 --> 18:37.283
Or were you just afraid that...

18:37.492 --> 18:39.661
...you were gonna lose me?
DAMON: Honestly?

18:40.203 --> 18:41.996
Bit of both.

18:44.833 --> 18:46.042
Yeah.

18:46.251 --> 18:47.961
Well, here's what I'm afraid of.

18:48.253 --> 18:52.382
I'm afraid that if you do take it,
you'll lose something else that you love.

18:52.549 --> 18:54.759
Heh, being a vampire.

18:55.009 --> 18:58.221
We're not gonna be happy
if you resent me for the rest of our lives.

18:58.471 --> 19:01.349
I don't know. I'm pretty sexy
when I'm resentful.

19:02.517 --> 19:04.769
Seriously. Come on, Damon.

19:07.021 --> 19:09.357
Are you ready to give all this up?

19:19.117 --> 19:20.577
To be continued.

19:20.743 --> 19:22.412
I want to show you something.

19:22.620 --> 19:24.247
Where are we going?

19:24.414 --> 19:27.375
Well, down, for starters. Unless you want
to wuss out and take the stairs.

19:27.542 --> 19:28.710
[CHUCKLES]

19:28.877 --> 19:33.089
- Ah, you only live once, right?
- Once or twice.

19:33.298 --> 19:34.883
[CHUCKLES]

19:41.472 --> 19:42.891
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

19:48.605 --> 19:51.900
It's bad form to drink a thousand-dollar
bottle of bourbon by yourself.

19:55.445 --> 19:57.155
So you're really doing this, huh?

19:57.405 --> 19:58.615
Taking the plunge.

19:59.657 --> 20:02.285
- Starting a family here.
- Yeah.

20:02.452 --> 20:04.787
- Guess that's the plan.
- Want some drunk advice?

20:05.038 --> 20:08.166
- Sure.
- I've got 30 stitches in my side.

20:08.416 --> 20:11.628
All my friends are killers, except you.

20:12.795 --> 20:16.424
You're a human. Which means it's
a miracle you're still alive.

20:17.634 --> 20:20.470
You're a dick if you're okay
with bringing a kid into this.

20:20.678 --> 20:23.598
Well, if that's your bachelor toast,
it really sucks.

20:24.474 --> 20:25.642
Leave town.

20:25.808 --> 20:26.976
That's my advice.

20:27.143 --> 20:30.939
Take your happy fiancÃ©e,
your unborn baby and your miracle life...

20:31.940 --> 20:32.982
...and get out.

20:34.484 --> 20:36.152
Before it's too late.

20:39.155 --> 20:41.491
You left dinner
because you weren't feeling well.

20:41.658 --> 20:44.327
You won't remember anything unusual
that happened here.

20:44.494 --> 20:45.620
Now, go home.

20:48.581 --> 20:50.166
[ENZO SIGHS]

20:50.333 --> 20:54.128
Broken glassware, the overwhelming
scent of fresh blood.

20:54.337 --> 20:56.381
I see the family reunion went
without a hitch.

20:56.631 --> 20:59.717
What took you so long? I had to compel
the entire restaurant myself.

20:59.968 --> 21:02.845
I was looking for Damon.
Word is, he took off to find Elena.

21:03.096 --> 21:06.015
He's not picking up his cell phone now.
It's just you and me.

21:06.182 --> 21:09.644
Just you and me. Tsk. Aw.

21:09.811 --> 21:11.479
Has a nice ring to it, doesn't it?

21:12.146 --> 21:14.357
Suppose we ought to get used to it.

21:14.607 --> 21:18.278
- What the hell are you talking about?
- Ah.

21:18.861 --> 21:20.363
That's right.

21:20.613 --> 21:22.532
You haven't heard.

21:22.699 --> 21:24.200
Damon has the cure.

21:24.409 --> 21:27.662
And if we're to believe his bluster,
he plans on taking it with Elena.

21:29.539 --> 21:30.665
[CHUCKLES]

21:30.832 --> 21:34.168
I think I would know if my brother
were planning on turning human.

21:34.377 --> 21:38.715
Based on the look of shock
on your face, you don't.

21:40.300 --> 21:41.384
[SIGHS]

21:41.551 --> 21:44.929
So we can either stand here
and debate the merits of Damon's word...

21:45.179 --> 21:50.059
...or we can split up and find your mom
before she rips their heads off.

21:50.351 --> 21:51.394
Which is it gonna be?

21:56.733 --> 21:58.651
Bad news. Damon hijacked Elena.

21:58.860 --> 22:01.029
So do you wanna
take this party somewhere else?

22:01.237 --> 22:03.406
Yes. To my bed. If I can walk.

22:03.573 --> 22:05.742
[FOOTSTEPS]

22:07.577 --> 22:08.911
Oh, my God.

22:12.165 --> 22:13.791
Good evening, Ms. Bennett.

22:14.917 --> 22:19.797
I was out for a walk and I saw you through
the window and I thought, "I know her.

22:20.423 --> 22:23.176
That young lady ruined my life."

22:23.384 --> 22:24.427
Who is this?

22:24.677 --> 22:25.762
Lily Salvatore.

22:25.928 --> 22:27.221
Be careful.

22:27.430 --> 22:29.807
Bonnie destroyed something
very dear to me.

22:30.058 --> 22:32.602
And now all I feel is insatiable hunger.

22:32.769 --> 22:35.980
I didn't do it to spite you, Lily.
I did it to keep Kai trapped.

22:36.230 --> 22:39.609
Surely there's another way
to rescue my friends.

22:39.817 --> 22:43.905
There is no other way.
And even if I could help, I wouldn't.

22:45.531 --> 22:46.783
[JO GASPS]

22:48.951 --> 22:50.578
[BOTH GRUNTING AND GROANING]

22:56.626 --> 23:00.421
Now, let it go and get out.

23:02.131 --> 23:03.674
[GASPING]

23:04.926 --> 23:06.010
Your mistake.

23:13.976 --> 23:15.353
No, please.

23:15.603 --> 23:17.355
I'm pregnant!

23:17.522 --> 23:18.689
[PANTING]

23:24.112 --> 23:26.114
[HEARTS BEATING]

23:28.491 --> 23:29.617
Twins.

23:30.827 --> 23:31.953
What?

23:32.161 --> 23:33.996
Good luck to you.

23:38.459 --> 23:39.836
[GASPS]

23:42.505 --> 23:44.340
[GROANING]

23:44.841 --> 23:46.384
Stay calm. I'm gonna help you.

23:46.634 --> 23:48.970
DAMON: <i>What's your favorite thing
about being a vampire?</i>

23:49.554 --> 23:53.891
I guess if I had to choose one thing,
it would be that I can heal people.

23:54.058 --> 23:57.645
- Heh, said no vampire ever.
- Heh.

23:57.895 --> 24:00.690
Okay. Well, then enlighten me.

24:00.898 --> 24:03.860
I like all of it. The speed. The feed.

24:04.068 --> 24:05.570
Everything's so heightened.

24:07.071 --> 24:10.783
And eternally looking great in a black
leather jacket's not the worst thing either.

24:10.950 --> 24:12.869
[CHUCKLES]

24:13.870 --> 24:16.038
I'm forgetting something though.

24:16.914 --> 24:20.209
Hmm... Oh, I remember.

24:21.210 --> 24:24.046
Getting in people's heads
is quite a bit of fun too.

24:34.056 --> 24:35.433
My old house.

24:37.310 --> 24:40.813
You won't remember this, but this is
the first place I ever kissed you.

24:41.022 --> 24:44.442
Another very happy memory
Ric scrubbed from your brain.

24:44.609 --> 24:45.943
[ELENA CHUCKLING]

24:48.321 --> 24:49.489
[SIGHS]

24:51.073 --> 24:53.117
But this isn't real.

24:54.243 --> 24:56.412
It's a fantasy.

24:57.747 --> 24:59.332
You put this in my brain.

25:00.333 --> 25:01.459
Isn't that the point?

25:02.335 --> 25:04.128
I mean, as epic as this life is...

25:04.921 --> 25:07.423
...I'd be giving up so much more
if we didn't do this.

25:08.424 --> 25:11.594
I've had so much fantasy in my life, Elena.

25:12.428 --> 25:14.555
Enough for a hundred lifetimes.

25:16.724 --> 25:19.060
I'd give it all up for one life with you.

25:25.775 --> 25:29.278
- You brought it with you.
- Well, I wasn't gonna leave it in the soap dish.

25:29.445 --> 25:30.613
[CHUCKLES]

25:34.617 --> 25:36.369
I want this, Damon.

25:36.577 --> 25:40.373
No matter how much it scares me,
I can't pretend that I don't.

25:40.581 --> 25:44.085
I know you do. You've wanted this
since the day you became a vampire.

25:44.293 --> 25:46.963
- But for you, there's no going back.
- Never been my style.

25:47.129 --> 25:50.299
- And you're impulsive. And reckless.
- And madly in love with you.

25:52.009 --> 25:54.595
Forever, no matter how long
that's gonna be.

25:54.804 --> 25:57.598
And taking this cure, Elena,
won't change that.

26:01.811 --> 26:04.689
I'm ready for a little reality if you are.

26:20.413 --> 26:21.956
I love you.

26:23.833 --> 26:26.127
Till death do us part.

26:30.715 --> 26:32.174
Bottoms up.

26:40.182 --> 26:41.851
[SIGHING]

26:52.403 --> 26:53.446
How do you feel?

26:54.155 --> 26:55.740
I don't know.

26:56.699 --> 26:58.284
I, ah, kind of feel...

27:06.083 --> 27:07.627
- Looks so good.
- Looks good.

27:07.835 --> 27:09.003
- Sorry.
- You first.

27:09.170 --> 27:10.212
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

27:10.379 --> 27:12.214
How about eggplant parmesan?

27:12.798 --> 27:15.426
- You're an eggplant girl, huh?
- Is that bad?

27:15.635 --> 27:16.844
You don't like eggplant.

27:17.637 --> 27:19.347
Love it. Just taking notes.

27:19.930 --> 27:22.558
- Mental notes.
- For what? Our second date?

27:22.808 --> 27:26.312
No, I was thinking five-year anniversary.

27:29.649 --> 27:30.733
Hang on.

27:30.941 --> 27:33.527
I'm gonna get you home.
You're gonna be all right.

27:35.112 --> 27:37.823
Elena, hey.

27:39.200 --> 27:40.826
Hey.

27:41.577 --> 27:42.828
[SIGHS]

27:42.995 --> 27:44.538
You scared the crap out of me.

27:45.331 --> 27:46.666
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

27:46.832 --> 27:48.501
I think I'm okay.

27:49.001 --> 27:51.837
- What happened?
- We were on our first date.

27:52.546 --> 27:54.840
- What?
- Heh, yeah.

27:56.008 --> 27:57.968
[GASPING AND GRUNTING]

28:05.726 --> 28:09.980
Damon. Damon,
I'm getting my memories back.

28:13.734 --> 28:15.486
Damon, the cure.

28:15.695 --> 28:17.738
It undid the compulsion.

28:19.949 --> 28:22.535
- It worked.
- Yeah.

28:23.285 --> 28:24.787
Wait.

28:30.334 --> 28:31.502
[GRUNTS]

28:31.669 --> 28:32.753
[CHUCKLING]

28:34.630 --> 28:36.132
It's not healing.

28:36.716 --> 28:40.553
Damon, it's not healing.
That means it worked.

28:40.761 --> 28:41.971
It worked.

28:42.179 --> 28:43.431
[SOBBING]

28:43.681 --> 28:45.391
How you feeling about that?

28:45.599 --> 28:47.143
I feel...

28:48.394 --> 28:50.604
I feel like I wanna kiss you.

28:54.734 --> 28:56.736
[PHONE RINGING]

28:57.319 --> 28:58.612
Hang on.

28:59.238 --> 29:00.656
Ah, Stefan.

29:01.532 --> 29:04.827
Better be good, brother.
Elena and I are having a moment.

29:05.035 --> 29:06.912
Damon, do not take that cure.

29:07.913 --> 29:09.415
What?

29:10.166 --> 29:13.419
- How do you even know?
- Lily got away. It's a bad time to be human.

29:13.586 --> 29:15.171
- What's going on?
STEFAN: <i>You're right.</i>

29:15.421 --> 29:18.966
- We gotta lock her up.
- What is he saying? I can't hear anymore.

29:20.885 --> 29:22.595
Apparently Mama Salvatore...

29:22.762 --> 29:24.263
- Ugh.
- Aah!

29:27.600 --> 29:31.228
I'm sorry, but I won't be imprisoned again.

29:31.937 --> 29:33.981
I didn't have to turn into this person.

29:34.190 --> 29:36.108
I kept her at bay for so long.

29:37.485 --> 29:40.613
But my sons, they ruined everything.

29:41.280 --> 29:43.991
- They were just trying to help.
- Look at me.

29:45.659 --> 29:47.703
They're not helping.

29:50.956 --> 29:52.958
You're bleeding.

29:54.293 --> 29:55.336
You took the cure.

29:57.963 --> 30:00.466
- You're human.
- You don't want to feed on me.

30:01.842 --> 30:03.719
- Yes, Elena.
- Please.

30:04.512 --> 30:05.805
- I do.
- No.

30:06.847 --> 30:08.140
- No!
- Ugh.

30:08.307 --> 30:09.809
[GROANING]

30:16.982 --> 30:19.318
[GASPING AND PANTING]

30:40.589 --> 30:41.966
[GRUNTING]

30:43.717 --> 30:45.886
Really? Come on.

30:46.846 --> 30:48.514
[GROANING AND GRUNTING]

30:59.525 --> 31:01.110
LILY:
Elena.

31:05.114 --> 31:06.448
[PANTING]

31:10.327 --> 31:11.495
[GRUNTING]

31:13.414 --> 31:15.499
Focus.

31:24.341 --> 31:26.510
[PANTING]

31:32.641 --> 31:33.684
No.

31:33.893 --> 31:35.269
It's okay. It's okay.

31:35.519 --> 31:38.397
Usually we don't yank out
penetrating objects, but don't worry.

31:38.564 --> 31:41.233
Squeeze my hand
if you have trouble breathing.

31:41.400 --> 31:44.028
No squeeze? Good. That's really good.

31:44.236 --> 31:45.529
Come on, up. Up.

31:47.531 --> 31:49.283
No, no. Don't try and talk.

31:49.533 --> 31:51.702
I heard what she said. Twins.

31:51.911 --> 31:54.246
Means I'm number one
on Kai's most wanted list.

31:54.455 --> 31:56.874
Congratulations.
You have been bumped to number two.

31:57.082 --> 31:59.919
So thank you for destroying
that stupid Ascendant.

32:00.169 --> 32:03.213
I hope you meant what you said,
there's no way out of that prison.

32:03.422 --> 32:06.091
I promise. He's not getting out.

32:07.301 --> 32:09.428
Worst bachelorette party ever, right?

32:09.595 --> 32:11.055
Let's get to the hospital.

32:11.221 --> 32:13.891
ELENA [OVER PHONE]: <i>I got out through
the tunnels. She came through the Grill.</i>

32:14.058 --> 32:15.225
<i>She might still be there.</i>

32:15.392 --> 32:17.937
We're right outside, so get home.
We'll deal with her.

32:18.103 --> 32:20.898
- Elena's safe. Get up. We need
to find Lily. DAMON: Ugh, ugh.

32:21.106 --> 32:25.444
Yeah. Oh, I'm fine. Thanks for asking.

32:27.196 --> 32:32.242
So were you gonna tell me or was it just
easier to be your normal, dickish self?

32:32.451 --> 32:35.913
- What do you think?
- I think being human is the last thing you want.

32:36.914 --> 32:38.791
I want to be with Elena, Stefan.

32:40.918 --> 32:44.505
Do you have any idea what it feels like
for me? To have to hear it from Enzo?

32:44.755 --> 32:47.549
To have no say
as to whether I lose my brother or not?

32:47.716 --> 32:49.134
[DAMON GRUNTING]

32:49.301 --> 32:52.638
Of course I know what it feels like.
Why do you think I didn't tell you?

32:54.848 --> 32:56.433
Can we go find our mother?

32:59.144 --> 33:01.313
[SOBBING]

33:08.821 --> 33:10.990
LILY:
Look what you've done to your mother.

33:11.365 --> 33:13.033
[SOBBING]

33:13.242 --> 33:14.535
I'm a mess.

33:14.785 --> 33:20.666
In a few days, or months, or years,
you'll feel different.

33:21.875 --> 33:24.670
What does it matter if I'm alone?

33:26.296 --> 33:28.841
Terrified of falling off the edge?

33:31.343 --> 33:34.680
I suppose I'd be like you, wouldn't I?

33:35.472 --> 33:38.517
Sad and alone.

33:42.354 --> 33:44.064
[GASPS]

33:51.196 --> 33:54.033
No, no, no. You don't want to do that.

33:54.199 --> 33:55.534
Please don't do that.

33:55.784 --> 33:58.495
Stay alive for us. Your sons.

33:58.704 --> 34:02.875
The ones who I know that deep down inside,
you still care about.

34:06.920 --> 34:09.214
And who still care about you.

34:13.844 --> 34:15.804
You're looking into my eyes.

34:19.891 --> 34:22.061
You always had such pretty eyes.

34:27.858 --> 34:30.152
[ALL GRUNTING]

34:35.239 --> 34:36.324
[GASPING]

34:36.492 --> 34:37.909
You okay?

34:51.215 --> 34:54.092
- Oh, my God.
- It's okay. It's not my blood. It's okay.

34:55.761 --> 34:58.764
- How's Bonnie?
- She's fine. Damon gave her some of his blood.

34:58.972 --> 35:01.850
What about you? How are you?
How's the baby?

35:12.611 --> 35:13.987
Babies, actually.

35:14.738 --> 35:17.199
Turns out there's two of them
cooking in there.

35:18.951 --> 35:20.452
Twins.

35:21.787 --> 35:23.288
Okay.

35:23.580 --> 35:25.833
Look, the more the merrier.

35:25.999 --> 35:27.501
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

35:28.627 --> 35:31.880
Even if Kai never escapes that prison...

35:32.798 --> 35:35.801
...my family is gonna try
and take them from us.

35:36.677 --> 35:40.806
A new Gemini twin merge is the only thing
that can strip Kai of his power.

35:41.014 --> 35:42.349
We won't let them find out.

35:44.017 --> 35:45.060
How is that possible?

35:45.310 --> 35:48.021
Because after the wedding,
we're gonna disappear.

35:48.772 --> 35:51.483
We're gonna go somewhere
where your family can't find us.

35:51.692 --> 35:56.196
Alaric, I can't ask you
to give your whole life up for me.

35:57.364 --> 36:00.367
You, the baby...

36:00.534 --> 36:01.577
Babies.

36:01.827 --> 36:03.871
...you are my life.

36:04.580 --> 36:07.082
And all I care about is keeping you safe.

36:22.681 --> 36:24.558
Good news from the front lines.

36:24.808 --> 36:27.227
Bonnie is okay, Jo is okay...

36:27.394 --> 36:31.398
...and Lily has been laid down
for a long winter's nap.

36:33.567 --> 36:36.195
- You look lost in thought.
- I remember everything.

36:36.403 --> 36:37.571
Every moment.

36:37.821 --> 36:42.367
It's like a million tiny, little pieces
of my heart have fallen back into place.

36:42.576 --> 36:45.621
I remember the moment that we met.
The moment that we fell in love.

36:45.871 --> 36:49.041
How much I didn't want to love you,
but it was like...

36:49.249 --> 36:52.044
It was like I was being swept up
into a current.

36:52.252 --> 36:54.963
- I was consumed by it.
- That's a good thing, right?

36:55.214 --> 36:58.258
Damon, I remember everything. Every kiss.

36:58.425 --> 36:59.927
Every conversation.

37:00.928 --> 37:03.889
- I still don't see how that's bad, heh.
- Heh.

37:04.097 --> 37:06.266
We've already had this discussion, Damon.

37:07.267 --> 37:08.393
About the cure.

37:09.144 --> 37:11.980
- On the island.
- What? No.

37:12.231 --> 37:13.649
That was totally different.

37:13.899 --> 37:16.401
Was it? Because I remember it
like it was yesterday.

37:17.110 --> 37:18.779
Take the cure with me.

37:20.572 --> 37:22.950
That's how much I know this is real.

37:23.116 --> 37:25.994
That's how certain I am
that I'm gonna love you...

37:26.245 --> 37:28.997
...even after this is all over.

37:29.248 --> 37:30.958
Take the cure.

37:32.292 --> 37:33.794
Be human with me.

37:34.294 --> 37:36.004
You know, I used to miss being human.

37:36.797 --> 37:40.259
Now I can't think of anything
more miserable on Earth.

37:41.134 --> 37:44.137
ELENA: <i>You walked away from me.
You didn't want me to change your mind.</i>

37:44.388 --> 37:47.599
- Because you don't want this.
- Hey. That was a long time ago.

37:47.849 --> 37:50.227
- You haven't thought this through.
- What? No.

37:50.435 --> 37:54.439
You're so afraid of losing me, you've convinced
yourself you can endure a human life...

37:54.648 --> 37:57.359
- Don't tell me what to think.
- Stefan, what does he think?

37:57.567 --> 38:00.153
I don't care what Stefan thinks.
I've made up my mind.

38:00.404 --> 38:03.782
I'm not gonna have him drown me in guilt
and have me change my mind.

38:03.991 --> 38:05.951
Damon. I love you.

38:06.159 --> 38:08.662
More than I ever thought
was humanly possible.

38:10.372 --> 38:13.917
I'm not trying to hurt you,
but I can't let you do this.

38:14.084 --> 38:19.589
Not before you've let everyone in your life
try to talk you out of it. Including you.

38:43.530 --> 38:44.990
LILY:
Hello?

38:48.702 --> 38:49.953
Look who's awake.

38:53.123 --> 38:54.791
Lorenzo? Is that you?

38:55.000 --> 38:57.919
Just wanted to make sure
you were in good hands.

38:59.171 --> 39:01.214
[WHIMPERING]

39:04.426 --> 39:07.637
Let me out so we can speak
like civilized people.

39:07.846 --> 39:09.306
STEFAN:
That's not gonna happen.

39:09.806 --> 39:11.016
I can take it from here.

39:11.850 --> 39:13.018
She's fragile.

39:13.226 --> 39:15.312
She should be around someone she trusts.

39:17.064 --> 39:20.359
I said, I can take it from here.

39:21.985 --> 39:23.487
[SIGHS]

39:25.155 --> 39:28.575
I'll come visit, Lily.
This is a family matter now.

39:43.673 --> 39:46.343
You know, earlier you asked me
what it'd feel like...

39:46.551 --> 39:51.014
...to have something I cherished
for 150 years ripped away from me.

39:53.475 --> 39:56.728
You're right, I'd be devastated.

39:58.522 --> 39:59.898
A little late to win me over.

40:00.107 --> 40:04.111
It's never too late.
That's the upside of eternity.

40:04.361 --> 40:06.863
You'll be my mother for the next century.

40:07.072 --> 40:09.533
And the one after that
and the one after that.

40:09.741 --> 40:13.245
And one day, maybe not soon...

40:14.413 --> 40:16.039
...but one day...

40:18.083 --> 40:20.043
...you'll see me as your son.

40:30.637 --> 40:31.721
LILY:
Stefan.

40:33.932 --> 40:36.768
You have no idea
what devastation feels like.

40:39.062 --> 40:40.230
But you will.

40:40.397 --> 40:43.525
Because I'm going to find a way
to get my people back.

40:45.235 --> 40:47.529
No matter what it takes.

40:56.121 --> 40:58.123
[KAI WHISTLING "SHINE"]

41:19.936 --> 41:21.396
[SIGHS]

41:21.563 --> 41:23.565
[BELL DINGING]

41:25.609 --> 41:27.486
Come and get it.

41:29.988 --> 41:33.450
Big breakfast for a big day.

41:48.673 --> 41:51.384
It's time we get the
hell out of this place.

41:55.472 --> 41:56.806
[LAUGHS]

42:27.837 --> 42:29.839
[English - US - SDH]
